    <section class="article-content">
    
    
    <p>摘要：威尼斯建筑双年展展示了建筑产业的镜像，提出了“循环经济宣言”来应对气候危机，展示了由植物、动物、矿物等材料制成的轻量级、生物降解的结构。这项名为VAMO的项目结合了自然、人工和集体智能，展示了数字工具与人类创造力的结合，以及建筑材料的循环利用。该项目的结构集成了多种废弃物材料，展示了创新设计和可持续发展的理念。</p>
<p>主题标签：建筑设计创新、可持续发展、数字技术应用</p>
<h2 id="原文链接">原文链接
</h2><p>VAMO proposes an alternative to architectural permanence
<a class="link" href="https://news.mit.edu/2025/vamo-proposes-alternative-architectural-permanence-0701"  target="_blank" rel="noopener"
    >https://news.mit.edu/2025/vamo-proposes-alternative-architectural-permanence-0701</a></p>
<h2 id="原文摘要">原文摘要
</h2><p>The International Architecture Exhibition of La Biennale di Venezia holds up a mirror to the industry — not only reflecting current priorities and preoccupations, but also projecting an agenda for what might be possible. </p>
<p>Curated by Carlo Ratti, MIT professor of practice of urban technologies and planning, this year’s exhibition (“Intelligens. Natural. Artificial. Collective”) proposes a “Circular Economy Manifesto” with the goal to support the “development and production of projects that utili&hellip;</p>

</section>


